{
  "texts": [
    "However, along with the precision of recommendation, they also raise concerns regarding the system's opacity since it is tough for the users to understand why they come across specific content (Zhang & Chen, 2020).",
    "Previous studies on social media recommendation systems focus on various domains such as efficacy and user satisfaction (Guy et al., 2010), estimation accuracy (Bilgic & Mooney, 2005), the effectiveness of different types of explanations in context-aware applications, the intelligibility of instant messenger notifications and context-aware applications (Lim & Dey, 2011), the effect of accuracy on trust in machine remodels (Yin et al., 2019), explainable media recommendations (Zhao et al., 2019), and explainable artificial intelligence (XAI)-based fake news and hate speech detection in social media (Mehta & Passi, 2022).",
    "Although a recommendation system's accuracy (performance) is one of the performance metrics of model interpretability/explainability, a model's stated accuracy can differ in real-world use due to differences between training and real-world data.",
    "Additionally, model accuracy significantly impacts users' trust, although that also depends on users' domain knowledge and observation abilities (Yin et al., 2019).",
    "Furthermore, previous scholarly contributions on the explainable social media recommendation also primarily dominated by the hate speech detection domain (Ahmed & Lin, 2024; Mehta & Passi, 2022), explainable fake news detection using humans and algorithms (Bunde, 2021; Dabbous et al., 2022; Snijders et al., 2023), and collaborative viewpoint-based regression in explainable recommendation (Chien et al., 2022), etc."
  ]
}